                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2466</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Oral Statement Handed by the Japanese Ambassador</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nomura</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> on November 17, 1941</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-17"
                            >17–11–1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Japanese Ambassador has been authorized to state that the Japanese Government
                    has no objection whatever to apply the principle of political stabilization to
                    the entire area of the Pacific and that the Japanese Government is willing to
                    eliminate the word “southwestern” from the text of Article VI of its proposal of
                    September 25th.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
